This work deals with the one-dimensional Hubbard model. It has seven
chapters: 1. Introduction; 2. The Hubbard Model; 3. Algebraic Representation
for the Hilbert Space of the 1D Hubbard Model; 4. Pseudoparticle Perturbation
Theory; 5. Excitations and Finite-Size Effects; 6. Zero-Temperature Transport;
7. Conclusions.